Patch Set 3:

@afazekas, can you share the reproduced steps? I'm interested in that. Thanks for working on this.

Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

TBH I have little concern for the performance, under current implementation all notification message be sent by one qpid connection and I agree this could cause some race issue under heavy concurrent situation without necessary lock protection. But after your change, glance-api need connect to qpid every time when upper layer code emit each message, generally the connection establishment is an expensive operation for whole stack (Operation System+Lib+PID), it involved a lot of resource allocation and process handling, so I consider it will be better if we just use OS's lock mechanism to prevent this dead lock issue.

I agree you using select and thread module of eventlet to make improvement on low level of cause, it make sense to me.

Patch Set 3:

https://github.com/openstack/glance/commit/60be7133544afa5e63c0b742d31b9998688530b6

The re-connection NOT added by this change. I just made it thread safe.

I agree a connection reuse would be a better solution, but the original code did not reused the connection.

Probably a proper fix would be using the oslo rpc, but it is much bigger change (including config options), and I do not think it is fits into this cycle.

As you can see without additional patching  the connection reuse is not working.
https://bugs.launchpad.net/glance/+bug/1100317

Patch Set 3:

16 times higher focused load survived than originally in total.

Patch Set 3: No score

1. I agree with you to make this thread safe and enable select module patch as this patch did is needed. But I still consider connection reuse mechanism will be better.

2. Since we will landing oslo.messaging asap when it ready in Icehouse cycle, so if we want to land this change down we'd better do it in H (mark this as a rc bug). I prefer it go this way.

In general, the substance of this change looks good and I would be inclined to +2 it after these minor nit-picks are handled.

Thanks!
